Event description

Description

Elevator Dance Music

Experienced jazz trumpet player and producer, Barabás Lőrinc, has played in a variety of formations (Nicola Conte, Valerie June) both in his home town of Budapest and throughout the world.

The unik repertoir of Barabás Lőrinc is based on the albums of the concept of Elevator Dance Music (2015) and Sastra (2013). The musician plays the concert alone: keyboard, trumpet, laptop and loop station are his instruments.

Groovy, uplifting dance with echoes of electro pop is spiced up with the compelling sound of the trumpet. The crossover of sounds and styles, electrifying currents of electro funk and deeply rhythmic melodies and arpeggios align to create high energy dance music from the spotless mind of a jazz musician.
